<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870226-0082 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Cleveland Electric Illuminating Co.</HL><DD> 02/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BOND MARKET NEWS (BON) </IN><TEXT>   CLEVELAND ELECTRIC ILLUMINATING CO. said it will sell $300 million of first mortgage 9 3/8% bonds. The 30-year bonds will be offered at 99 3/8 to yield 9.438%, the Cleveland-based utility said. Proceeds from the sale will be used to redeem first mortgage bonds at a total price of $84 million, to pay short-term debt and for general purposes, the utility said. </TEXT></DOC>